olive oil
2 potato
1 leek
2 clove garlic
1 carrot
1 tin chickpeas
40 g plant-based butter
2 tablespoon (tbsp) plant-based milk
20 g plant-based butter (for the sauce)
1 sachet Mild Caribbean Jerk Seasoning
1 packet tomato paste
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
1 packet coconut milk
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 packet coriander
1 packet beef mince

• Bring a medium saucepan of salted water to the boil.
• Peel potato, then cut into large chunks. Thinly slice leek. Finely chop garlic. Grate carrot. Drain and rinse half the chickpeas.

• Cook potato in the boiling water, over high heat, until easily pierced with a fork, 10-15 minutes. Drain and return to the saucepan.
• Add the plant-based butter (for the mash), plant-based milk and a generous pinch of salt, then mash until smooth. Cover to keep warm.

• Meanwhile, heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook beef mince, leek and carrot, breaking up with a spoon, until browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Add plant-based butter (for the sauce), garlic, mild Caribbean jerk seasoning and tomato paste and cook until fragrant, 2 minutes.
• Add rinsed chickpease, vegetable stock powder and coconut milk and simmer until thickened, 2-3 minutes. Season with pepper.
• Stir through baby leaves until wilted, 1-2 minutes.

• Preheat grill to high.
• Transfer chickpea filling to a baking dish, then top with potato mash. Run a fork over mash to create an uneven surface.

• Grill pie until lightly browned, 10-15 minutes.

• Divide Caribbean coconut chickpea, beef and veggie pie with mash topping between plates.
• Tear over coriander to serve. Enjoy!